<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1917-12-26T17:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1917-12-26T17:00:00-05:00" n="629" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d629">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 763.72/8262</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss>
                                    to the Minister in China</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_RPS1" type="to"><hi rend="italic">Reinsch</hi></persName>)</head>
                            <opener>
                                <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                            </opener>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1917-12-26T17:00:00-05:00">
                                        <hi rend="italic">December 26, 1917, 5 p.m.</hi>
                                    </date>
                                </dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>Your December 23, 1 p.m. For your information and guidance. The
                                President, and State, War and Treasury Departments all favor
                                financial assistance to China for military expedition. The matter
                                awaits approval of the Allied Council. What is foundation of your
                                statement that Allies have agreed to the policy?</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <persName corresp="#p_LR1">
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Lansing</hi>
                                    </persName>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>